    <TD><font face="verdana,arial" size=2>
		<p>
		<b>NOTE:</b> The following installation procedure is valid ONLY for the 2nd Generation beta <font color="red"><b>2.0.1</b></font>.
		<p>
		
			<b>1.</b> Uncompress  the CARE2X 2nd Generation beta 2.0.1 scripts into the active directory of your server.
			<p>
			<b>2.</b> Make the following directories and files  system writeable.

<blockquote>
/cache/barcodes/<br>
/counter/hits/<br>
/counter/hitcount.txt<br>
/fotos/encounter/<br>
/fotos/news/<br>
/fotos/registration/<br>
/logs/  (and all its subdirectories)<br>
/med_depot/img/<br>
/pharma/img/<br>
/radiology/dicom_img/<br>
/gui/img/logos_dept/<br>
<font color=#ff0000>/gui/smarty_template/templates_c/ (and all its subdirectories)</font>
</blockquote>
<p>
			<b>3.</b> Enter the host, database name, username, and password information in the <b><font color=#ff0000>include/inc_init_main.php</font></b> script:  <p>
			Change the following three secret keys with unique keys of
			your choice. <P>
			<blockquote>
			$key           : The secret key for the first level script lock.<br>
			$key_2level  : The secret key for the second level script lock.<br>
			$ley_login     : The secret key for the third level script lock.<P>
			</blockquote>
			For the main domain, enter the domain or host name without the http:// or https:// part and without a trailing slash as value of the $main_domain variable:<P>	
			<P>
			If you are running Care2x in an SSL server, make sure that the $httprotocol variable in this script is set to "https".
			<p>			
			<b>4.</b> Set the variable <b>$dbtype</b> value depending on the database you are using:
			<ul>
				$dbtype = 'mysql';   // for mySQL database<p>
				$dbtype = 'postgres7'; // for PostgreSQL database
				 
			</ul>			<p>
			<b>5.</b> Open the <b>global_conf/inc_remoteservers_conf.php</b> script. 
			<blockquote>
			If necessary, you can set the webcam source url's here.
			</blockquote>
			<p>
			<b>6.</b> Create the database.
			<p>
			<b>7.</b> Load the following dump depending on the database you are using:<p>
<blockquote>			
				For mySQL database ---> <font color=#ff0000>install/mysql/manual/care_db_structure_b201_manual_my.sql</font>  <p>
				For PostgreSQL database ---> <font color=#ff0000>install/postgres7/manual/care_db_structure_b201_manual_pg.sql</font><p>
</blockquote>			
			<p>The following 4 dump files are for the <b>german</b> icd codes! Do not load them if you do not need the german codes.
<blockquote>            install/sql/icd10_de/a2g-insert.sql<br>
			install/sql/icd10_de/h2n-insert.sql<br>
			install/sql/icd10_de/o2s-insert.sql<br>
			install/sql/icd10_de/t2z-insert.sql
<P>
			<FONT COLOR=#FF0000>Note: If you prefer to load the CSV formatted data, download the CSV file from here:
			<A HREF="https://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=53886&release_id=204455" TARGET="_blank">care_icd10_de.csv</A></FONT>
</blockquote>	
		
			<p>The following 2 dump files are for the <b>english</b> icd codes! Do not load them if you do not need the english codes.
<blockquote>			install/sql/icd10_en/insert-data-a2l.sql<br>
			install/sql/icd10_en/insert-data-m2y.sql<br>
<p>
			<FONT COLOR=#FF0000>Note: If you prefer to load the CSV formatted data, download the CSV file from here:
			<A HREF="https://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=53886&release_id=204455" TARGET="_blank">care_icd10_en.csv</A></FONT>
		</blockquote>	
			<p>The following 2 dump files are for the <b>brazilian-portuguese</b> icd codes! Do not load them if you do not need the brazilian-portuguese codes.
<blockquote>			install/sql/icd10_br/insert-data-a2l.sql<br>
			install/sql/icd10_br/insert-data-m2z.sql<br>
			<p>
			<FONT COLOR=#FF0000>Note: If you prefer to load the CSV formatted data, download the CSV file from here:
			<A HREF="https://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=53886&release_id=204455" TARGET="_blank">care_icd10_pt_br.csv</A></FONT>
</blockquote>
		<p>The following 2 dump files are for the <b>spanish</b> icd codes! Do not load them if you do not need the spanish codes.
<blockquote>			
			install/sql/icd10_es/insert-data-a20.sql<br>
			install/sql/icd10_es/insert-data-p2z.sql<br>
</blockquote>
		<p>The following 2 dump files are for the <b>bosnian/latin</b> icd codes! Do not load them if you do not need the bosnian/latin codes.
<blockquote>			
			install/sql/icd10_bs/insert-data-a2l.sql<br>
			install/sql/icd10_bs/insert-data-m2y.sql<br>
</blockquote>
			<p>The following 3 dump files are for the <b>german ops</b> codes! Do not run them if you do not need the german ops codes.
		<p>
<blockquote>            install/sql/ops301_de/insert-data-1-5-499.sql<br>
			install/sql/ops301_de/insert-data-55-57.sql<br>
			install/sql/ops301_de/insert-data-58-94.sql<br>
			<p>
			<FONT COLOR=#FF0000>Note: If you prefer to load the CSV formatted data, download the CSV file from here:
			<A HREF="https://sourceforge.net/project/showfiles.php?group_id=53886&release_id=204460" TARGET="_blank">care_ops301_de.csv</A></FONT>
</blockquote>	

			<p>The following dump is for the <b>spanish ops</b> codes! Do not run them if you do not need the spanish ops codes.
		<p>
<blockquote>            install/sql/ops301_es/insert-data-1.sql<br>

</blockquote>	


 </blockquote><p>
			<b>8.</b>  Create a new system admin  permission.<p>
		<blockquote>	
		 You need to use the supplied <font color=#ff0000>create_admin.php</font> script. Type http://your_host/create_admin.php in your browser.
		 Enter the necessary information and hit the button. Important: After creating the new system admin, remove this script from your active server directory.
		 Leaving it in the active server directory will cause Care2x to block and refuse to run.
			</blockquote><p>
			
		 <b>9.</b> REMOVE THE FOLLOWING FILES FROM THE CARE2X DIRECTORY!<p>
		<blockquote>	
		 <li>/create_admin.php<br>
		 <li>/install/install.php<br>
		 <li>/install/initialize.php<br>
		 <li>/install/encode_pw_md5.php<p>
		 Tip: you can move them to other places outside the web server directory.
			</blockquote><p>
			
			<b>10.</b> The installation is finished. Enter the following address in the browser:
			<blockquote>
			http://your_host/ <p>(where your_host is the actual host address of your Apache web server). 
			The first page of CARE 2X should appear. Congratulations!
		<p>Now you can start  creating user access permissions. <p>
			To do this:<p>
	Select the EDP link on the left menu
			and then select "Access rights". Enter your admin username and your admin password. When the 
			interface appears, you can start creating user access rights and permissions.
			<p>Note: You cannot create additional Admin permission
			using this interface. You have to follow the step #8
			 to create additional admin permissions.
</blockquote>				</blockquote>
		
		<B>11.</B> Configure Care2x => <A HREF="en_configure_11.htm" TARGET="_blank">go here</A>
		
</P></TD></TR>
